                            <comment id="13104358" author="srowen" created="Wed, 14 Sep 2011 09:43:57 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;I agree that looks like an error. Who&apos;s the author &amp;#8211; can I just turn off the combiner?&lt;br/&gt;
Or we can leave the combiner, but when used as such, it can only sum and not filter.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13104374" author="philoc" created="Wed, 14 Sep 2011 10:20:42 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Agree with U!&lt;br/&gt;
And turn off the combiner does work! That&apos;s the easiest way, even though this may hurt the efficiency, but not serious.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13104375" author="srowen" created="Wed, 14 Sep 2011 10:22:05 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Bleh, easy enough I just fixed it by separating out the combiner.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
